<section id="demos">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="sec-head"><h2>Built with Robium</h2><span class="count">3 reference apps · green on every run</span></div>
    <p class="lead">
      Real applications, built by the skills with minimal intervention — the
      regression suite, the starter kits, and the proof, all at once. Take one,
      or build something entirely your own. All of them live in
      <a href="https://github.com/robium-ai/robium-applications">robium-applications</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="spots">
      <article class="spot">
        <div class="spot-body">
          <span class="spot-kicker">Mobile navigation</span>
          <h3>nav-trial</h3>
          <p class="claim">A TurtleBot maps its world with SLAM, then navigates it — headless, in your browser.</p>
          <p>
            TurtleBot 3 builds a map with slam_toolbox, then Nav2 drives goals on
            the saved map — fully headless on a MacBook, visualized live through
            Foxglove.
          </p>
          <p class="stack">ROS 2 Jazzy · Nav2 · slam_toolbox · Gazebo Harmonic · Docker (arm64) · Foxglove</p>
          <a href="/demos/nav-trial/" class="go">Try the live demo</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="spot">
        <div class="spot-body">
          <span class="spot-kicker">Vision-language-action</span>
          <h3>vla-trial</h3>
          <p class="claim">Type an instruction. A VLA model drives a simulated arm.</p>
          <p>
            SmolVLA drives a simulated SO-101 arm from natural language —
            cameras, joints, and actions on a scrubable Rerun timeline. Ships
            with the scripted oracle that recorded its training data; the full
            fine-tune is still in progress and the demo says so honestly. Runs
            on your machine today; hosted version coming.
          </p>
          <p class="stack">LeRobot 0.6.0 · SmolVLA 450M · MuJoCo 3.10 · Rerun 0.34 · Gradio 6 · HF Jobs</p>
          <a href="/demos/vla-trial/" class="go">Try the live demo (local)</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="spot has-media">
        <div class="spot-body">
          <span class="spot-kicker">Imitation learning</span>
          <h3>manip-trial</h3>
          <p class="claim">A policy trains and evaluates with metrics — on a GPU-less laptop.</p>
          <p>
            An ACT policy trains on the PushT dataset and evaluates in sim. The
            live demo is a checkpoint ladder: the same policy at 1k/3k/5k/10k
            steps, runnable side by side. Right: a real evaluation rollout.
          </p>
          <p class="stack">LeRobot 0.6.0 · ACT policy · gym-pusht · uv · Apple-silicon MPS</p>
          <a href="/demos/manip-trial/" class="go">Try the live demo (local)</a>
        </div>
        <div class="spot-media">
          <video src="/media/pusht-eval.mp4" autoplay loop muted playsinline></video>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

